TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ben-Rephael, Azi
AU  - Oded, Jacob
AU  - Wohl, Avi
T1  - Do Firms Buy Their Stock at Bargain Prices? Evidence from Actual Stock Repurchase Disclosures*
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rft028
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 18
IS  - 4
SP  - 1299
EP  - 1340
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Using new monthly data, we investigate open-market repurchase executions of US firms. We find that firms repurchase at prices that are significantly lower than average market prices. This price discount is negatively related to size and positively related to market-to-book ratio. Firms’ repurchase activity is followed by a positive and significant abnormal return. Importantly, the market response occurs when firms disclose their actual repurchase data in earnings announcements, and this positive response is followed by a 1-month drift. Consistent with these results, we find that insider trading is positively related to actual repurchases.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rft028
ER  - 



